quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord will be gardens of perpetual residence beneath which rivers flow, wherein they will abide forever, Allāh being pleased with them and they with Him. That is for whoever has feared his Lord."
  99,1,"When the earth is shaken with its [final] earthquake"
  99,2,"And the earth discharges its burdens<sup foot_note=197793>1</sup>",footnotes:197793:1
  99,3,"And man says,<sup foot_note=197794>1</sup> "What is [wrong] with it?" -",footnotes:197794:1
  99,4,"That Day, it will report its news"
  99,5,"Because your Lord has inspired [i.e., commanded] it."
  99,6,"That Day, the people will depart<sup foot_note=197795>1</sup> separated [into categories] to be shown [the result of] their deeds.",footnotes:197795:1
  99,7,"So whoever does an atom's weight<sup foot_note=197796>1</sup> of good will see it,",footnotes:197796:1
  99,8,"And whoever does an atom's weight of evil will see it."
  100,1,"By the racers, panting,<sup foot_note=197797>1</sup>",footnotes:197797:1
  100,2,"And the producers of sparks [when] striking<sup foot_note=197798>1</sup>",footnotes:197798:1
  100,3,"And the chargers at dawn,<sup foot_note=197799>1</sup>",footnotes:197799:1
  100,4,"Stirring up thereby [clouds of] dust,"
  100,5,"Arriving thereby in the center<sup foot_note=197800>1</sup> collectively,",footnotes:197800:1
  100,6,"Indeed mankind, to his Lord, is ungrateful."
  100,7,"And indeed, he is to that a witness.<sup foot_note=197801>1</sup>",footnotes:197801:1
  100,8,"And indeed he is, in love of wealth, intense."
  100,9,"But does he not know that when the contents of the graves are scattered"